@node Top
@top setenv-file

Set or unset environment variables from an "env" file.

This package provides two interactive functions:

@enumerate
@item
@samp{setenv-file-set}: set all the env vars in an env file
@item
@samp{setenv-file-unset}: unset all the env vars in an env file
@end enumerate

When used interactively, each function prompts for a file. By default, the
prompt begins at @samp{setenv-file-dir}.
@end ifnottex

