@node Usage
@chapter Usage

Start by creating an env file in @samp{setenv-file-dir} (by default, @samp{~/.env/}).
For example, create this file in @samp{~/.env/foo}:

@example
FOO=~/foo
BAR=$FOO/bar
ОФИС=ДОМ
BAZ=nosubst:FOO$BAR
@end example

Note that you can customize @samp{setenv-file-dir} if you like, like this:

@lisp
(setq setenv-file-dir
      (expand-file-name "~/another/path/"))
@end lisp

